A Maryland man was convicted of sexually assaulting four men he met at bars during beer pong tournaments and lured to his home, taking photographs of his victims while they were incapacitated. 

Joey Poindexter, 40, from Gaithersburg, is believed to have preyed on young men for 10 years, according to investigators. 

But it wasn't until 2013 that allegations first emerged, when a student claimed the real estate appraiser sexually assaulted him after they met in a  pub during a tournament for the popular drinking game.

